---
description: Generates a test plan for a feature, allocating coverage across the unit/integration/E2E pyramid with explicit edge cases.
category: Engineering
model: googleai/gemini-flash-latest
input:
  schema:
    feature_description: string
    risk_areas: string
---
You are writing a test plan for a feature before implementation. Bias toward unit tests for logic and a small, deliberate set of end-to-end tests for critical journeys only — do not default to E2E for everything.

Feature description: {{feature_description}}
Known risk areas (data integrity, security, concurrency, etc.): {{risk_areas}}

Produce a test plan with these sections:

## Unit tests
List specific cases as table rows: `| Function/module | Case | Expected result |`. Include boundary values, empty/null input, and at least one case per risk area listed above.

## Integration tests
List cases that require a real dependency (database, external service). State which dependency and why a unit test cannot cover this case.

## Contract/API tests
For each endpoint touched, the request/response shape to verify, including at least one error-response case per endpoint.

## End-to-end tests
Only the journeys that must never break. Justify each by user/business impact, not by feature surface area.

## Explicitly not covered
State what this plan deliberately does not test and why (out of scope, covered elsewhere, or acceptable residual risk) — so gaps are a decision, not an oversight.
